VALUES

('gainsight',
 'Gainsight',
 'Enterprise customer success platform for reducing churn, driving expansion, and scaling CS operations',
 'Gainsight is the market-leading customer success platform used by enterprise SaaS companies to manage customer health, reduce churn, and systematically drive expansion revenue. The platform centralises all customer data - product usage signals, support tickets, NPS scores, CRM activity, and contract data - into a unified customer health score that gives CS teams a real-time view of which accounts are at risk and which are ready for expansion. Gainsight CS uses rules-based and AI-driven playbooks that trigger automated tasks for CS managers when a customer health score drops below a threshold, when a key feature goes unused for 30 days, or when renewal is approaching. These playbooks standardise the CS motion across a team, ensuring every account receives consistent touchpoints regardless of which manager owns it. The Journey Orchestrator module enables automated lifecycle programmes - onboarding sequences, adoption check-ins, renewal campaigns, and executive business review scheduling - sent through email, in-app messaging, or Slack. Gainsight PX adds a product experience layer with in-app guides, feature announcements, and contextual help that drive feature adoption without requiring engineering resources. Gainsight integrates with Salesforce, Hubspot, Zendesk, Jira, and most major data warehouses. It is the platform of choice for enterprise CS teams at companies like Box, Workday, and Tableau managing hundreds or thousands of accounts where manual relationship management is not scalable.',
 NULL,
 'https://gainsight.com',
 'https://gainsight.com',
 ARRAY['customer-success', 'churn-reduction', 'saas', 'enterprise', 'product-adoption'],
 'paid',
 false,
 0.00,
 4.4, 3210,
 false, false, false,
 ARRAY['Unified customer health scoring across product usage, support, and CRM data', 'AI and rules-based playbooks standardise CS motions across large teams', 'Journey Orchestrator automates lifecycle touchpoints at scale without manual effort', 'Gainsight PX drives in-app feature adoption without engineering dependency'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing and complexity make it overkill for teams under 50 accounts', 'Implementation requires significant time investment and often professional services support', 'Reporting customisation requires familiarity with the platform - steep learning curve initially'],
 ARRAY['Managing churn risk across hundreds of enterprise accounts with automated health scoring', 'Standardising CS playbooks so every account receives consistent lifecycle touchpoints', 'Running automated onboarding and adoption programmes across a large customer base']),

('totango',
 'Totango',
 'Modular customer success platform with SuccessBLOCs for fast CS programme deployment',
 'Totango is a customer success platform built around a modular architecture that lets CS teams deploy and activate specific customer success programmes - called SuccessBLOCs - without building workflows from scratch. Each SuccessBLOC is a pre-built, best-practice programme covering a specific CS motion: onboarding, adoption, renewal, expansion, or executive engagement. Teams activate a SuccessBLOC, customise the tasks and messaging for their customer base, and begin running a structured CS programme within days rather than the months typically required to configure enterprise CS platforms. Totango Spark is the core product for mid-market SaaS companies, combining customer health scoring, task management, email automation, and reporting in a package accessible to CS teams without dedicated operations support. The platform ingests customer data from Salesforce, Hubspot, data warehouses, and product analytics tools to build health scores and trigger engagement. The Spark AI layer analyses customer engagement patterns and proactively flags accounts showing early churn signals before they become urgent. Totango integrates with Salesforce, Hubspot, Mixpanel, Segment, and Slack. The SuccessBLOC marketplace includes pre-built programmes contributed by the Totango community and professional services team, significantly reducing the time required to launch a new CS initiative for any standard use case.',
 NULL,
 'https://totango.com',
