('catalyst',
 'Catalyst',
 'Customer success platform with deep Salesforce integration and revenue-first CS programme management',
 'Catalyst is a customer success platform built for CS teams that operate within a Salesforce-centric revenue stack and need their CS data to live natively alongside CRM data rather than in a disconnected system. The platform is built on top of Salesforce infrastructure, which means customer health scores, CS tasks, playbooks, and account intelligence appear directly within Salesforce records without requiring a data sync or integration layer. This architecture eliminates the data discrepancy problems that arise when CRM and CS platforms operate separately - a customer renewal date changed in Salesforce immediately reflects in the CS health scoring, and CS activity logged in Catalyst is immediately visible to account executives in their CRM workflow. Catalyst tracks customer health across product adoption, support engagement, executive sponsorship, and NPS data, with automated playbooks that trigger tasks based on health threshold breaches. The platform includes revenue forecasting for CS teams - projecting renewal probability and expansion pipeline from health data, giving CS leadership a data-driven view of net revenue retention. Catalyst integrates natively with Salesforce and connects to Segment, Amplitude, Mixpanel, and Zendesk for product and support data ingestion. Used by CS teams at Outreach, Salesloft, and Yext where Salesforce is the system of record and CS data needs to be accessible to the entire revenue team without platform switching.',
