('userpilot',
 'Userpilot',
 'Product growth and customer success platform for user onboarding, feature adoption, and in-app engagement',
 'Userpilot is a product growth platform that gives product and customer success teams the ability to build in-app onboarding experiences, feature announcements, tooltips, and surveys without engineering resources. The platform targets the adoption gap that exists between a user signing up and actually achieving value from the product - the period where most SaaS churn originates. CS and product teams use Userpilot to build guided onboarding flows that walk new users through key setup steps, contextual tooltips that explain unfamiliar features when users encounter them, and NPS surveys triggered after meaningful product events. The segmentation engine lets teams target different onboarding tracks to different user personas - an admin user gets a different onboarding flow than an end user, and an enterprise customer sees different feature announcements than a self-serve SMB. Userpilot Analytics tracks feature adoption rates, funnel completion, and user engagement patterns across segments, giving CS and product teams data on which onboarding flows drive activation and which leave users stuck. The platform requires no code to build or update in-app experiences after an initial lightweight installation. Userpilot integrates with Amplitude, Mixpanel, Segment, Hubspot, Salesforce, and Intercom. Used by product and CS teams at Attest, Kontentino, and Bynder to accelerate time-to-value and drive feature adoption across their active user base.',
